<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871012-0159 </DOCNO><HL> Letters to the Editor:Government NeedsA Good Education</HL><DD> 10/12/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><TEXT>   The page-one article (Sept. 28) on commercial firms finding themselves forced to spend money and time to teach elementary subjects to prospective employees is one of the most damning indictments of our public-school system. It's about time we started seriously to phase out the public schools and establish incentives, such as tax credits, to encourage the establishment of profit-oriented and tax-exempt private schools, as well as parochial schools. Education is too important a function to be left in the hands of the government.    Oscar B. Johannsen   Roselle Park, N.J.</TEXT></DOC>